actual.value:
1. During the reporting period. 70 female social workers from Women Care Directorate in the Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs. and social workers of different CSOs whom nominated by the NGOs directorate/COMSEC are capacitated on providing psychosocial support for women survivors from conflicts.  to enable women SFBV survivors to tell their stories. record their needs. make their demands in a safe and culturally appropriate ways. and guide them on how to handle challenges such as the potential re-traumatization of victims. 

2. According the Women Care Department within MOLSA. 330 cases of victims have been supported by the female social workers who were trained under the project;
3. IRP has produced an analytical study on how to re-design existing MOLSA protocols to strengthen victim assistance policies. The study has been finalized. submitted and approved by MOLSA.
